Package rbvs.product

Class ExtendedProduct

  • java.lang.Object
    • rbvs.product.Product
      • rbvs.product.SimpleProduct
        • rbvs.product.ExtendedProduct
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, IProduct, IShoppingCartElement
    public class ExtendedProduct
extends SimpleProduct
    Implementation of a product with with a name and price. Offers an undo operation to revert the last change of the internal state.

    Attributes of the class:

    • ExtendedProduct representing the state previous to the last modification.

      • setName

        public void setName​(String name)
        Sets the name of the product. The passed name can be null or an empty string. If the passed name is null the name is initialized with an empty string.

        Before the name change, the current state is stored so this action can be reverted.

        Specified by:

      • setPrice

        public void setPrice​(float price)
              throws IllegalArgumentException
        Sets the price of the product.

        If a negative value is passed the method will throw an IllegalArgumentException. This Exception contains an error description consisting of a brief description of the cause and the illegal argument value.

        Before the price changes, the current state is stored so that this action can be reverted.

        Specified by:

      • deepCopy

        public ExtendedProduct deepCopy()
        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 
         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements. While it is typically the case that: 
         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.

        NOTE: The savedState is not considered by this method.
